      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Glass and Ceramic Shipping</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Glass tableware, artwork, decorative items, and other ceramics are extremely fragile. Honeycomb cardboard's superior shock absorption and compression resistance make it ideal for protecting these items. The lightweight nature also helps manage shipping costs for products with relatively low density but high fragility.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Machinery and Equipment Export</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Heavy machinery requires robust protection during long-distance shipping. Honeycomb cardboard provides the strength needed to support machinery weight, protect surfaces from damage, and absorb vibrations during transportation. Industrial manufacturers rely on honeycomb panels for equipment export where protection is non-negotiable.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Electronics and Precision Instruments</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Electronics and precision instruments require shock protection combined with vibration damping. Honeycomb cardboard provides both, protecting delicate electronic components and ensuring instruments arrive in calibration during export shipments.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">International Export Packaging</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Products shipped internationally endure rough handling, multiple transfers, and extended transit times. Honeycomb cardboard provides the premium protection necessary to ensure products arrive undamaged despite the rigors of international logistics networks.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Custom Protective Solutions</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Honeycomb cardboard can be custom-cut and formed into specialized protective solutions for uniquely shaped products. Fabricators can create corner guards, protective sleeves, bracing systems, and support structures tailored to specific products.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Honeycomb vs Corrugated -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Honeycomb vs Standard Corrugated Cardboard</h2>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Understanding how honeycomb cardboard compares to standard corrugated helps you make the right material choice for your applications.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-2xl p-6 my-8">
        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Comparison Overview</h3>
        <ul class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4 space-y-3 list-inside">
          <li><strong>Strength:</strong> Honeycomb is 3x stronger; ideal for heavy loads</li>
          <li><strong>Weight:</strong> Honeycomb is lighter; reduces shipping costs</li>
          <li><strong>Cost:</strong> Honeycomb costs more per unit; justified for high-value items</li>
