        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">When to Use Standard Corrugated</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Standard corrugated cardboard is appropriate for routine shipments of less fragile items, cost-sensitive applications, and B2B packaging where protection is adequate rather than premium. The cost savings justify use for high-volume, lower-value shipments.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">When to Choose Honeycomb</h3>
      <p class="font-body text-lg text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Choose honeycomb for fragile items, valuable products, long-distance international shipping, heavy machinery, and situations where damage costs would exceed honeycomb material costs. The premium protection prevents costly damage claims and customer dissatisfaction.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Sizes and Specifications -->
