    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions About Honeycomb Cardboard</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 my-10">
        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">How much does honeycomb cardboard cost compared to foam or plastic?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Honeycomb cardboard typically costs less than high-quality foam or plastic protective materials while providing equivalent or superior protection. The recyclable nature also appeals to environmentally conscious businesses. While more expensive than standard corrugated, honeycomb justifies the cost for high-value items where damage prevention is essential.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">Is honeycomb cardboard recyclable?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Yes, honeycomb cardboard is fully recyclable. It's made entirely from kraft paper and follows standard recycling processes. Many businesses appreciate honeycomb's environmental benefits—superior protection without the non-recyclable concerns of foam or plastic. This makes honeycomb an excellent choice for companies with sustainability commitments.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">How is honeycomb cardboard manufactured?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Honeycomb cardboard is manufactured by spiral-winding kraft paper into hexagonal cells, then laminating these cores between kraft paper liners using adhesive. Industrial equipment ensures consistent cell structure and strength. The manufacturing process is mature and well-established, ensuring consistent quality across different producers.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">Can honeycomb panels be cut to custom shapes?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Yes, Quinocycle arranges custom cutting of honeycomb panels to specialized shapes and sizes. Fabricators use sharp tools or specialized equipment to cut honeycomb without damaging the cell structure. Custom cutting adds to lead time (typically 2-3 weeks) but allows creation of perfectly fitted protective solutions for uniquely shaped products.</p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-surface-variant/30 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-xl p-5 cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-variant/50 transition-colors">
          <summary class="font-headline font-bold text-on-surface">Does honeycomb cardboard protect against moisture?</summary>
          <p class="font-body text-secondary mt-3 leading-relaxed">Standard honeycomb cardboard provides moderate moisture protection. The kraft paper liners resist light moisture, but extended exposure to wet conditions can damage the structure. For moisture-sensitive applications or humid environments, request specialty kraft paper liners with water-resistant coatings. Contact Quinocycle about moisture-resistant honeycomb options.</p>
